FBIS3-11667 "drlat057_c_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-057 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Mar 1994 MEXICO Colosio Shot, Killed in Attack During Tijuana Campaign Stop 24 March Day of Mourning PA2403123994 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 1215 GMT 24 Mar 94 PA2403123994 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] At approximately 0515, President Salinas de Gortari decreed that Thursday, 24 March, will be a day of national mourning. All Mexican flags will fly half-mast at public buildings, schools, banks, and at all municipal palaces in Mexican towns as a sign of mourning over the death of Luis Donaldo Colosio.
